                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1114">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.4016/281</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-24T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 24, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2600. Department’s 2484, May 9, 4 p. m. Department has received further
                    information from French Ambassador relative to serious conditions Syria.
                    Investigate this matter promptly, and if information secured by you agrees with
                    that furnished by the French Ambassador, you are instructed, at once, without
                    waiting for further word from the Department, to urge the Ottoman Government to
                    take steps for the protection of Christians in Syria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
